🔹 What is Nikto?

    -Nikto is an open-source web server scanner.

    -It scans web servers for:

        Outdated software versions

        Dangerous files or scripts

        Insecure server configurations

    -Common vulnerabilities (e.g., default credentials, insecure headers, etc.)

    -It supports over 6700 checks for known issues.

🔹 Why use Nikto?

    -To identify misconfigurations in web servers.

    -To find potential entry points for attackers.

    -To detect outdated software that may have known vulnerabilities.

    -To perform quick reconnaissance in penetration testing.

🔹 How to use Nikto in Kali Linux (basic commands)

Check if Nikto is installed:

    nikto -h

(If not installed: sudo apt install nikto -y)

Scan a target website:

    nikto -h http://example.com

Scan using SSL (HTTPS):

    nikto -h https://example.com

Scan a specific port:

    nikto -h http://example.com -p 8080

Save results to a file:

    nikto -h http://example.com -o result.txt

Save in specific format (HTML, CSV, XML):

    nikto -h http://example.com -o result.html -Format html

🔹 Example output

When scanning, Nikto may report things like:

“Server leaks inodes via ETags, header found…”

“/phpinfo.php found, should be removed.”

“Outdated Apache version detected (2.4.41).”
